{"title_page": "Ripley County, Indiana", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox U.S. county\n| county           = Ripley County\n| state            = Indiana\n| seal             =\n| founded          = December 27, 1816\n| seat wl          = Versailles\n| largest city wl  = Batesville\n| area_total_sq_mi = 448.06\n| area_land_sq_mi  = 446.43\n| area_water_sq_mi = 1.64\n| area percentage  = 0.37%\n| census estimate yr = 2018\n| pop              = 28521\n| density_sq_mi    = 65\n| density_km2      = 24.93\n| time zone        = Eastern\n| footnotes = Indiana county number 69<br>FIPS Code 137\n| named for        = [[Eleazer Wheelock Ripley]]\n| district         = 6th\n| ex image         = Ripley County Courthouse, Versailles, IN (48467486191).jpg\n| ex image cap     = Ripley County Courthouse in Versailles\n}}\n'''Ripley County''' is a [[County (United States)|county]] located at the southeastern corner of the [[U.S. state]] of [[Indiana]]. According to the 2010 Census, the population was 28,818.<ref name=QF>{{cite web|url=http://quickfacts.census.gov/qfd/states/18/18137.html|title=Ripley County QuickFacts|accessdate=September 25, 2011|publisher=United States Census Bureau}}</ref> The [[county seat]] is [[Versailles, Indiana|Versailles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.naco.org/Counties/Pages/FindACounty.aspx|accessdate=June 7, 2011|title=Find a County|publisher=National Association of Counties}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nRipley County was formed on December 27, 1816, in the same legislative act that created [[Jennings County, Indiana|Jennings County]]. It was named for Gen. [[Eleazer Wheelock Ripley]], an officer in the [[War of 1812]], who figured in the [[Battle of Lundy's Lane]] and the [[Siege of Fort Erie]] during 1814.<ref>{{cite book|author=De Witt Clinton Goodrich & Charles Richard Tuttle|publisher=R. S. Peale & Co.|year=1875|location=Indiana|title=An Illustrated History of the State of Indiana|url=https://archive.org/details/anillustratedhi02tuttgoog|pages=[https://archive.org/details/anillustratedhi02tuttgoog/page/n584 572]}}</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nThe county seat of Ripley County is Versailles, Indiana. It was selected as the county seat in 1818, and was laid out in 1819.\n\nAccording to the 2010 census, the county has a total area of {{convert|448.06|sqmi}}, of which {{convert|446.43|sqmi}} (or 99.64%) is land and {{convert|1.64|sqmi}} (or 0.37%) is water.<ref name=\"census-density\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Overview of townships<ref>{{cite web|url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/GCTPH1.CY10/0500000US18137|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212201139/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/GCTPH1.CY10/0500000US18137|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 12, 2020|title=American FactFinder - Results|first=U.S. Census|last=Bureau|date=|website=factfinder.census.gov|accessdate=April 10, 2018}}</ref>\n|- style=\"background: rgb(204, 204, 204);\"\n!Township\n!Established Year\n!Area [[Square mile|mi\u00b2]]\n!Area [[Square km|km\u00b2]]\n!Population\n!Incorporated Towns\n|-\n|[[Adams Township, Ripley County, Indiana|Adams]]\n| align=\"center\" |1858\n| align=\"right\" |43.79\n| align=\"right\" |113.42\n| align=\"right\" |5119\n|[[Batesville, Indiana|Batesville]] (part), [[Sunman, Indiana|Sunman]]\n|-\n|[[Brown Township, Ripley County, Indiana|Brown]]\n| align=\"center\" |1823\n| align=\"right\" |53.67\n| align=\"right\" |139\n| align=\"right\" |1597\n|\n|-\n|[[Center Township, Ripley County, Indiana|Center]]\n| align=\"center\" |1858\n| align=\"right\" |29.51\n| align=\"right\" |76.43\n| align=\"right\" |2657\n|[[Osgood, Indiana|Osgood]]\n|-\n|[[Delaware Township, Ripley County, Indiana|Delaware]]\n| align=\"center\" |1823\n| align=\"right\" |33.27\n| align=\"right\" |86.17\n| align=\"right\" |1437\n|\n|-\n|[[Franklin Township, Ripley County, Indiana|Franklin]]\n| align=\"center\" |1823\n| align=\"right\" |36.6\n| align=\"right\" |94.79\n| ali